      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that if symptoms are gone, the bacteria are dead, is a common misconception. Even if symptoms have disappeared, some bacteria may still be present, and completing the antibiotic course helps ensure that all lingering bacteria are killed. Stopping early can increase the risk of drug-resistant bacteria developing. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and other reputable health organizations generally agree that finishing the full course is crucial to prevent this.",
